    @GetMapping(&quot;/app/submitted&quot;)
    public ModelAndView  submitted(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response, 
        @RequestParam(&quot;docId&quot;) String docId) {
      //...
      byte[] decodedDocIdBytes = Base64.getDecoder().decode(docId);
      String decodedDocIdAsString = new String(decoodDocIdBytes);

     }

Notice that docId has been changed to a String. 

As a side note - base64 code is not encryption, so if you really want to keep the docId&#39;s secret, I&#39;d look for another approach. If this is a REST(ish) API then the resource ID&#39;s (docIds) shouldn&#39;t have any external meaning, so there shouldn&#39;t be a requirement to hide them.

