You want to copy a range of four rows from the active spreadsheet (sheet = &quot;FromHere&quot;) to another spreadsheet (sheet = &quot;ToThere&quot;). The relationship between the two sheets is based on the Week Number in cell A1 of &quot;ToThere&quot; and which also appears in contiguous cells in Column B of &quot;ToThere&quot;.

You suggest that there are two criteria which would require an &quot;AND&quot; operator. However, there is only one criteria - the week number - and the task is to identify the first occurence of the matching week number in Column B of &quot;ToThere&quot;.

The overall process is:   
1 - find a match for the Week Number on &quot;ToThere&quot;

 - I used the Javascript method `indexOf` to find a match of the Week Number. `indexOf` returns the first index at which a given element can be found in an array, or -1 if it is not present. This required:
  - `var weekvalue = weekrange.getValue();` - get the Week Number from cell A1 of &quot;FromHere&quot;
  - `var ThereWeeks = ThereWeeksRange.getValues();` - get the values in the 2D array for Column B of &quot;ToThere&quot;
  - `var merged = ThereWeeks.reduce(function(a, b){return a.concat(b);});` - &quot;flatten&quot; the array to make it easier to find values
  - `var idx = merged.indexOf(weekvalue);` - find the first instance of the Week Number in Column B.

2) copy the values from &quot;FromHere&quot;    

 - `var weekdata = range1a.getValues();` - note this is the range &quot;B2:D5&quot;.
 
3) copy the values to &quot;ToThere&quot;   

 - `var weektarget = sheet2.getRange((+idx+1),3,4,3);` - get the range on &quot;ToThere&quot;
 - `weektarget.setValues(weekdata);` - update the value from &quot;FromHere&quot;

I have left several &quot;Logger&quot; statements in the code so that you can establish key values at critical points in the code.


----------


    function so5810174601() {
      
      var ss = SpreadsheetApp.getActiveSpreadsheet();
      var sheet1 = ss.getSheetByName(&#39;Sheet1&#39;);
      var ss2 = SpreadsheetApp.openById(&quot;1irUNEahhm1RM1LrpBR5d1SV1XPqwtdEhNkFu4E3meA4&quot;);
      var sheet2 = ss2.getSheetByName(&quot;Sheet2&quot;);
      
      // get the Week Number
      var weekrange = sheet1.getRange(&quot;A1&quot;); 
      var weekvalue = weekrange.getValue();
    	
      // get the week data 
      var range1a = sheet1.getRange(&quot;B2:D5&quot;)
      var weekdata = range1a.getValues();
    
      // get the values in Column B of &quot;ToThere&quot;     
      // get the last row
      var sheet2LR = sheet2.getLastRow();
      // define the range from row 1, Column 2(B), down to the last Row
      var ThereWeeksRange = sheet2.getRange(1,2,sheet2LR);
      // Logger.log(&quot;DEBUG: ThereWeeksRange = &quot;+ThereWeeksRange.getA1Notation());
      // get the values
      var ThereWeeks = ThereWeeksRange.getValues();
      // Logger.log(ThereWeeks); //DEBUG
      // flatten the 2D array
      var merged = ThereWeeks.reduce(function(a, b){return a.concat(b);});
      // find the first instance of the week Number in Column B
      var idx = merged.indexOf(weekvalue);
      // as long as the result isnt -1 (no match)
      if (idx !=-1){
        //Logger.log(&quot;DEBUG: the target row = &quot;+(+idx+1));
        // define the target range as row = index plus 1 (the index is zero based), Column = 3 (C), rows = 4 (A,B,C &amp; D), and Columns = 3 (TS,TC,TD)
        var weektarget = sheet2.getRange((+idx+1),3,4,3);
        // Logger.log(&quot;DEBUG: the sheet2 target range = &quot;+weektarget.getA1Notation());
        // update the range on &quot;ToThere from the range on &quot;FromHere&quot;
        weektarget.setValues(weekdata);
      }
      else{
        var ui = SpreadsheetApp.getUi();
        var response = ui.alert(&#39;Update Week Data&#39;, &#39;Could not find week number on &quot;ToThere&quot;. Aborting.&#39;, ui.ButtonSet.YES);
      }
    }

